citations:
    citation-agot-bran-vi:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Bran VI"
            text_from_source: "The Karstarks came in on a cold windy morning, bringing three hundred horsemen and near two thousand foot from their castle at Karhold … 'Twelve thousand men, or near enough as makes no matter,' said Maester Luwin."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Robb Stark's bannermen assemble at Winterfell. Lords present: Rickard Karstark (with sons Harrion, Eddard, and Torrhen), the Greatjon Umber, Roose Bolton, Galbart and Robett Glover, Maege Mormont, Lord Cerwyn, Lord Hornwood, Helman Tallhart, Theon Greyjoy. Total force approximately 12,000 men. Robb subdues the Greatjon after Grey Wind bites off two of his fingers. Bran acts as lord in Robb's place at feast. Osha warns in the godswood that Robb is marching the wrong way — north not south is the true threat. Robb gives command and rides south, leaving Bran as lord of Winterfell. The Greatjon is named to command the eastern host facing Tywin. Roose Bolton commands the eastern foot."
